column4: Tell me if anyone has any insight about this error I am getting : http://pastebin.com/m6feb6570
Updated the apt-get software itself? I may have as I ran apt-get upgrade two days ago
check that your /etc/sources.list file is good. Then run apt-get update.
I will look into that right now and let you know
and don't accept candy from strangers
good to know. By the way... the only repo in the course.list is : deb http://ports.ubuntu.com jaunty main restricted universe multiverse
I have ran that many times... it has not helpped
what are you trying to install?
Anything really... finch, Ntfs Read/Write support... they all throw errors
did you do an upgrade from 8.10 to 9.04?
No... it was already Jaunty. This is not a typical computer... its a Sheeva Plug... Im sure you have heard of them.
